<br>
Upon further consideration of the solution planned, monks in the endgame will still probably tank just as well as warriors even after the so-called nerf...<br>
<br>
Now why do I say that?<br>
<br>
Well, the whole idea behind Furor's original complaints was that monks took less DPS due to higher avoidance and equal mitigation.  This was true of course, due to higher block procs.<br>
<br>
Now, the nerf is supposed to reduce mitigation of monks, which it probably will across all levels of monks, while leaving their avoidance intact.  Sound good right?  Wrong.<br>
<br>
Basically, any high level mob in game, no level of AC will give you any kind of Mitigation.  We know this.  IE, doesn't matter what your AC is, Eom's, Seru, Emp, AL, etc will still hit you for max.  Right?<br>
<br>
So, what will lowering monk mitigation do?  Nada.<br>
<br>
We'll still get hit for about the same amount that everyone else is most likely.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, monk avoidance is going to remain the same.  IE, we'll still avoid 6% more than plate classes.  And still mitigate about the same as everyone else against those mobs, ie not at all.<br>
<br>
Translation, monks will still be rampage tanks.  Monks will still take less damage due to avoidance skills, maybe even less than currently if they beef up those skills.  We'll still do our normal DPS, except we might eat up some more of that precious healer mana.<br>
<br>
What will this really do to other monks?<br>
<br>
Well, this will probably leave monks soloing the same stuff they did before, still offtanking when necessary (as most high level monks will still be well above effective ac softcaps for experience groups), and still soloing.  After all, due to low monk hps avoidance really is better than mitigation, though a little more streaky.  Though, not like it's anything FD won't solve, right?)<br>
<br>
Sure, monks die a little more pulling due to avoidance skills not being applied when our backs are turned, but it's not like slower raids are a bad thing.  I mean, we all love long raids and longer CR's.<br>
<br>
In the end, what does this mean?  Plate classes are still relatively broken.  They still won't be any better off versus high level encounters.  Their taunt still sucks and they'll be dependent on EB and Hate giving weapons.  Verant has made alot of people unhappy.  And there's now alot more strife between classes.<br>
<br>
Good job Verant.<br>
<br>
And for all those who decided that cheering on the nerf of other classes was a good thing, well, I'm sure that you feel better now, right?<br>
<br>
All in all, looks like a win win situation for everyone.  I'm sure glad that Verant took this road instead of fixing actual AC mitigation above the effective softcaps.  Aren't you?<br>
<br>
LaotzuQigong<br>
60 Grandmaster<br>
Legendary<br>
