<br>
I think where the misconception lies is that monks should &quot;tank&quot; at all. A tank is a heavily armored, relatively slow beast that can take a punishing amount of damage and pays for this with a somewhat limited selection of firepower. Tanks do alot of damage, but not nearly the damage that non mobile emplacements do.<br>
<br>
A monk is not a tank, nor should he be. A monk is artillery. Artillery does shattering damage but is screwed if it actually gets hit. It's strength lies in not being hit, ie avoidance. <br>
<br>
The error lies with the conception that anyone besides knights and warriors should tank, period. Monks, like rogues and rangers, are meant to be stand off weapons that do tremendous damage at the price of an inability to take damage in kind.<br>
<br>
The problem is that because off the availability of armor that wasn't class restricted and had low weight, monks were approaching the mitigation abilities of the true tanks. In addition, they had superior avoidance abilities which, when matched with thier vast damage superiority, seriously overpowered them.<br>
<br>
As it stands now, with the ac softcap still in place, monks are still going to enjoy much the same survivability they always have had. They may not solo quite the mobs they did before, but I seriously doubt if you will ever find a warrior that will sympathise with someone who complains about a lack of solo'ing ability.<br>
<br>
Monks have needed to return to the niche the were intended to have for a long time...this patch will steer them in that direction. With some of the other upcomming changes in the next few patches and the addition of PoP, this gulf in tanking abilities should widen further and more firmly cement monks in the place they were originally supposed to occupy. My hope is that there will also be a widening of the difference between mitigation capabilities between knights and warriors as well. As I posted in another thread, there has been no direct indication that the softcap will be raised or removed in anything i've seen regarding the coming of PoP. However, there are strong suggestions, when other factors are taken into consideration, that this will indeed happen. There is going to be a major retuning of many current mobs before and during the PoP release. The release of information about the new AA's shows that the stat cap will definately be raised. There are also many items out there already that can be obtained from NToV and higher zones that already breach the softcap before buffs, with VT making it painfully simple. Verant has already stated that PoP gear and weapons will be the best in the game by measurable margin. Unless the softcap is raised, then there is nowhere to go with armor at all, which would make the gear upgrade pointless. Verant does alot of dumb things, but i seriously doubt they would introduce an entire expansion worth of gear that is completely pointless.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
Aielman KajiraLiege<br>
